sc0 ls0 ws0">that ask Him?&quot; Luke 11:13. </div><div class="t m13a x27 h2f y2c2 ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">STUDY HELP: &quot;The Desire of Ages,&quot; pp. 662-680. </div><div class="t m7f4 x40 h87 y1f78 ff1 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Promise of the Comforter </div><div class="t m48b x14 h1 y1714 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. </div><div class="t m1f6 x29 h1 y188b ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What promise of the Spirit was given through the prophet Joel? </div><div class="t mcae x27 h1 yfa6 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Joel 2:23, 28-32. </div><div class="t m8a8 x14 h2f y2172 ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">NOTE.—The </div><div class="t m67b x6 he y1d97 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">early rain came in Palestine in the autumn or early winter at </div><div class="t ma0a x27 he y19a7 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">sowing time to cause the grain to begin to grow. The latter rain came toward </div><div class="t m32b x27 he y1df9 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">spring for ripening the harvest. The promise in these last days is of the early </div><div class="t m417 x11 he yb50 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and latter rain, that the reaper may overtake the sower, and that the work </div><div class="t m80a x11 he y1db4 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">may be finished speedily. </div><div class="t mae7 x14 h1 y2f ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m18c3 x29 h1 y1934 ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What assurance did Christ give to His disciples? John 14:16, 17. </div><div class="t mab7 x5d he y198d ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">NoTE.—&quot;The Holy Spirit is Christ&apos;s representative, but divested of the </div><div class="t m7f2 x11 he yca2 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">personality of humanity, and independent thereof. Cumbered with humanity, </div><div class="t m5cb x11 he y82 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Christ could not be in every place personally. Therefore it was for their interest </div><div class="t m41b x11 he y196a ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">that He should go to the Father, and send the Spirit to be His successor on </div><div class="t m6e5 x11 he y1aab ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">earth. No one could then have any advantage because of his location or his </div><div class="t md5 x11 he y20b2 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">personal contact with Christ. By the Spirit the Saviour would be accessible </div><div class="t mefc x11 he yc34 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">to all. In this sense He would be nearer to them than if He had not ascended on </div><div class="t m5cb x11 he y449 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">high.&quot;—&quot;The </div><div class="t me38 x35 h21 y1622 ff6 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Desire of Ages,&quot; </div><div class="t m234f x8b h16 y1622 ff6 fs7 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">p. </div><div class="t m1dfd x2 h21 y22b8 ff6 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">669. </div><div class="t m334 x1b h2f yf19 ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">( 29 ] </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
